  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms </strong>are around 26-35m² and sleep up to three people (the extra bed is a single sofa bed). They are north or east facing with a balcony. </p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Twin Rooms </strong>are around 29m² and sleep two people. They have balcony with lovely Matterhorn view.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Single Rooms </strong>are around 26-28m² and are north or east facing with balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Twin Junior Suites with Matterhorn View</strong> are around 35m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). They have a balcony with Matterhorn view and seating area.</p>
<p><strong>Double Junior Suites</strong> are around 26-29m² and sleep two people. These suites are north or east facing and have a balcony and seating area.</p>
<p><strong>Alpine Junior Suites</strong> are around 32-35m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These suites have an open bath in the room, and a balcony with Matterhorn view.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Bath with showerhead</li>
<li>Bathrobes</li>
<li>Slippers</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>3pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. CHF 4.00 per person per night is payable locally (children aged 9-15 years pay a reduced rate of CHF 2.00 per person per night, and guests aged under 9 are exempt).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
